<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: FOUNTAIN VALLEY; FREE SAFETY FAIR WILL BE HELD SATURDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A "Community Safety Faire" -- featuring displays from the city's police and 
fire departments, American Red Cross, the California Highway Patrol and Orange 
County Search & Rescue -- will be held Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 The free event, sponsored by the Fountain Valley Disaster Preparedness 
Advisory Committee, will be held from 10 a.m. to 2 p.m. at the Sam's Club 
parking lot, 17099 Brookhurst St., south of Warner Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call Bob Hoxsie, event chairman, at (714) 968-8149 or 
Kathy Williams, city emergency preparedness coordinator, (714) 965-4424. 
</P>
</TEXT>
