<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO; RIDE THERAPY CENTER PLANS FUND-RAISER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The annual horse trail fund-raiser for the Fran Joswick Therapeutic Riding 
Center will be held on Saturday.  
</P>
<P>
 It's an opportunity to experience the scenic trails of San Juan Capistrano on 
horseback and help out the Joswick Center, which uses horses in a therapy 
program designed to help people recover from debilitating injuries. 
</P>
<P>
 The program starts at 8:30 a.m. and will also feature art, food and game 
booths, as well as refreshments. People wishing to take a trail ride during the 
fund-raiser must reserve them by calling (714) 240-8441. 
</P>
<P>
 Craig Powers, an on-air personality for radio KIK-FM, will present awards to 
horse show winners and sign autographs from 11 a.m. to 1 p.m. The center is at 
26282 Oso Road. 
</P>
<P>
 The event is a major fund-raiser for the Joswick Center, a nonprofit group 
that survives largely through the generosity of South County communities. 
</P>
<P>
 The center gives children and adults, some of whom use wheelchairs, a chance 
to be lifted onto the back of a horse and learn basic riding techniques. 
</P>
<P>
 Center officials say the horse rides are an important therapy tool that has 
helped many physically challenged people in its 16 years of existence. FRANK 
MESSINA 
</P>
</TEXT>
