<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: LEAGUE OF VOTERS TO HOST CONFERENCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JENNIFER KELLEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Ventura County League of Women Voters is hosting a conference titled 
"Social Issues and the Global Economy" on May 6 at the Ventura Doubletree 
Hotel. 
</P>
<P>
 Featured speakers will include Donald Villarejo of the California Institute 
for Rural Studies, Marilyn F. Solomon of UNICEF, and Jamshid Damooei of Cal 
Lutheran University. 
</P>
<P>
 The luncheon keynote speaker will be Joel Kotkin, author of "Tribes: How Race, 
Religion, and Identity Determine Success in the New Global Economy." 
</P>
<P>
 The conference fee is $35, which includes lunch. Checks should be sent to 
LWVVC, 6656 Sora St., Ventura, CA. 93003. For information, call 642-8078 or 
523-3488 after Monday. JENNIFER KELLEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
