<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: VOTER REGISTRATION DEADLINE IS MAY 9 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CARLOS V. LOZANO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura County election officials are reminding residents that May 9 is the 
deadline for registering to vote in the June 7 election. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents can obtain registration cards at city halls, libraries, fire 
stations and post offices, said Bruce Bradley, the county's chief elections 
official.  
</P>
<P>
 Among the local offices up for election are two east county supervisorial 
seats, county auditor-controller, county tax assessor, county clerk, county 
superintendent of schools and a seat on the Superior Court bench. County voters 
will also be casting ballots in two congressional primaries and four 
legislative primaries. CARLOS V. LOZANO 
</P>
</TEXT>
