<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP SOFTBALL ROUNDUP; FOSTER DELIVERS IN 12TH FOR SUNNY HILLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kate Foster had a run-scoring single in the 12th inning to give Sunny Hills a 
1-0 victory over Fullerton in a Freeway League softball game Thursday at Sunny 
Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 Foster's hit scored Jodi Brooks from second. Jennifer Dean pitched a 
four-hitter for Sunny Hills (11-8, 4-1 in league), which moved into first place 
at the halfway point. 
</P>
<P>
 In other Freeway League games: 
</P>
<P>
 Sonora 6, Buena Park 1 -- Tiffany Kind, who had a perfect game through six 
innings, struck out seven and gave up one hit to improve to 9-7 for host 
Sonora. Teri Bryant had two hits, including a bases-loaded triple, and scored 
once for Sonora (12-11, 3-3). 
</P>
<P>
 La Habra 2, Troy 0 -- Amber Duarte had three hits, one RBI and two steals and 
Edie Topping and Heather Tom each added two hits for La Habra (6-11, 2-4). 
Cristy Turner struck out three and gave up two hits for the Highlanders. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Century League: 
</P>
<P>
 Canyon 1, Santa Ana Valley 0 (8) -- Veronica Lopez, who pitched a one-hitter 
with six strikeouts for Canyon (12-5, 4-1), scored the game-winning run on a 
single by Jennifer Broughton in the bottom of the eighth inning. 
</P>
<P>
 Villa Park 1, El Modena 0 (9) -- Brandee McArthur pitched a one-hitter and 
doubled for Villa Park, which won in the ninth when Silvia Salgado walked, took 
second on a sacrifice, went to third on an error and scored on a wild pitch. 
Villa Park improved to 13-8 and 4-1 in league, and El Modena dropped to 7-12 
and 2-3 in league. 
</P>
<P>
 Foothill 2, Orange 1 (9) -- With two outs in the top of the ninth inning, 
outfielder Marissa Holmes singled home Amy Barnes for Foothill (17-6, 5-1). 
Holmes went two for three. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Garden Grove League: 
</P>
<P>
 Kennedy 3, Garden Grove 0 -- Lisa Pitt (14-1) struck out 10 and gave up four 
hits to earn her ninth shutout for Kennedy (17-4-1, 10-0-1). Laurie Fritz had 
two hits and an RBI for Kennedy. 
</P>
<P>
 La Quinta 8, Los Amigos 1 -- Michelle Weld gave up no runs on one hit through 
four innings and Jaclyn Fredrickson doubled, scored two runs and had two RBIs 
for La Quinta (15-5, 8-2). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Olympic League: 
</P>
<P>
 Whittier Christian 1, Brethren Christian 0 -- Debora Goddu (7-5) pitched her 
her fourth consecutive shutout for visiting Whittier Christian (8-6, 7-1). She 
had eight strikeouts. Goddu had a one-out triple in the seventh and scored on a 
single by Jody Miller. Michelle Reutter of Brethren Christian (11-5, 4-4) 
struck out eight. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Lutheran 6, Ontario Christian 3 -- Junior Michelle Harrison struck out 
10 and went two for four for Orange Lutheran (8-5, 3-4). Caroline Schulz also 
went two for four for Orange Lutheran. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Orange League: 
</P>
<P>
 Western 5, Anaheim 4 -- Andrea Salas had two hits and an RBI and Belen 
Hernandez gave up one earned run on six hits for Anaheim (1-13, 1-4). 
</P>
<P>
 Brea-Olinda 10, Magnolia 5 -- Gretchen Thompson was two for three, including 
one triple, and had two RBIs for host Brea-Olinda (7-10, 2-3). Coleen Clark had 
two RBIs for the Wildcats. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Pacific Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
 Trabuco Hills 2, Century 1 -- Junior Ann Marie Froysaa, who scored Trabuco 
Hills' first run, drove in Kelly Stout with the winning run in the bottom of 
the seventh. Natalie Galasso pitched a two-hitter with 10 strikeouts for the 
Mustangs. 
</P>
<P>
 Costa Mesa 12, Estancia 0 -- The county's leading hitter, Tabby Cleveland, 
went three for four with two RBIs and four stolen bases to lead Costa Mesa. 
Nicola Woody was three for four with two RBIs. 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Hills 10, Laguna Beach 2 -- Shortstop Misty Thompson was three for 
four, scored three runs and had two RBIs for Laguna Hills. Jessica Roache hit a 
two-run home run in third inning for host Laguna Beach (4-13, 0-6). 
</P>
</TEXT>
