<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: PACOIMA; RECREATION CENTER WILL OPEN IN PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIGUEL BUSTILLO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A recreation center offering everything from karate exhibitions to dance 
courses is set to open in Pacoima's Paxton Park by early June, park officials 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The facility, on 10736 Laurel Canyon Blvd., will probably be named the Ritchie 
Valens Community Center, said Paxton Park Director Art Gomez.Valens, who hailed 
from Pacoima, was a rock star. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's basically going to be a recreation center to meet the needs of the 
community, from preschool to adults," Gomez said. 
</P>
<P>
 The center will include a preschool, a gym, a stage and sound system, and 
possibly a day-care facility, Gomez said. 
</P>
<P>
 It will house dance classes for children and adults, karate and boxing classes 
and exhibitions, youth and adult basketball and volleyball leagues, and will be 
used as a multicultural conference center.  
</P>
<P>
 Pacoima's new Hispanic Chamber of Commerce will also meet at the center once a 
month, Gomez said. MIGUEL BUSTILLO 
</P>
</TEXT>
