<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISCHER TO JUMP IN COUNTY MEET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN ORTEGA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Region record-holders Jeremy Fischer of Camarillo High and Dolores Tuimoloau 
of Channel Islands top the list of competitors in the Ventura County track and 
field championships at Camarillo today. 
</P>
<P>
 Fischer, who raised his region record to 7 feet 4 inches in the high jump at 
last month's Santa Barbara Easter Relays, is shooting for his third consecutive 
meet title in that event and will be gunning for his second long jump victory 
in three years. 
</P>
<P>
 Tuimoloau, the defending meet champion in the discus, has been on a tear in 
the shotput this year. She opened the season with a personal best of 45-6 at 
the Spartan Relays on March 5 and has bettered that mark several times to reach 
48-10. 
</P>
<P>
 Sprinter Ramsey Jay of Ventura, distance runner Jeff Fischer of Thousand Oaks, 
weight-event performer Damon Blechen of Agoura and hurdler Andrea Wasden of Rio 
Mesa also are entered. JOHN ORTEGA 
</P>
