<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; RWANDA; MISSIONARY, ORPHANS SAFELY EVACUATED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Amelia Barbieri, the 76-year-old lay missionary who refused to abandon 
children trapped with her at an orphanage in violence-torn Rwanda, is home 
safely with 44 of her orphans, according to church officials in Rome.Barbieri 
and the children were evacuated by Italian relief organizations and sent to 
Bergamo in northern Italy. The children have been placed in a rehabilitation 
center in Verona. Meanwhile, in Washington, State Department deputy spokeswoman 
Christine Shelly urged government and military leaders in Rwanda to do 
"everything in their power" to end the violence that has claimed more than 
100,000 lives over the last three weeks. 
</P>
