<HEADLINE>
<P>
U.S. JET CRASHES IN ADRIATIC, PILOT DIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A U.S. pilot on a NATO mission to monitor and enforce a ban on military 
flights over Bosnia-Herzegovina was killed Thursday when his jet crashed 
shortly after takeoff from an aircraft carrier in the Adriatic Sea, officials 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The FA-18 jet left the Saratoga and plunged into the sea, the U.S. 6th Fleet 
said in a statement from Gaeta, Italy. 
</P>
<P>
 The pilot's body was recovered, but his name was withheld, the fleet said. The 
incident will be investigated, it said. 
</P>
<P>
 White House spokeswoman Dee Dee Myers expressed President Clinton's 
condolences. 
</P>
