<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: STANTON; SLAYING VICTIM'S IDENTITY DETERMINED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man found shot to death in the back seat of a car on Sunday has been 
identified as Gustavo Gomez, 31, a sheriff's official said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Lt. Dan Martini said investigators had difficulty identifying the victim, who 
had a lengthy arrest record, because he had at least six aliases. 
</P>
<P>
 Gomez, who had been shot in the head, was found in the 7300 block of Syracuse 
Street inside a 1985 Toyota that was registered under one of his aliases, 
Martini said. 
</P>
<P>
 "Because of his criminal history, we are looking into the possibility that 
this may have been the result of a drug deal gone bad," Martini said. "But at 
this point, we have nothing to confirm that." 
</P>
<P>
 The body was discovered when a neighbor called to report that the car had not 
been moved in two days. Martini said investigators believe that Gomez was 
killed at a different location, then left on Syracuse Street. 
</P>
</TEXT>
