ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; STUDENTS TO TAKE PART IN BUILDING CONTEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL BILLITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Soon under construction: a competition. 
</P>
<P>
 In a countywide contest being held Saturday and Sunday at the Tustin Market 
Place, 12 student teams will be building mini-houses from the ground up. 
</P>
<P>
 The event is the fifth annual Design/Build Competition, coordinated by the 
Home Builders Council. Contestants will be students from high schools and 
community colleges who are learning about the construction industry. 
</P>
<P>
 "The purpose of the Design/Build Competition is to provide hands-on 
construction experience that is unavailable in most high school classroom 
settings," said Janice Silverman, a spokeswoman for the event. "Professional 
building inspectors will inspect structures for compliance to building and 
safety codes. On Sunday, the structures will be judged by building-industry 
professionals, and awards will be presented." 
</P>
<P>
 The contest is from 8 a.m. to 4:40 p.m. Saturday and 8 a.m. to 2 p.m. Sunday 
at the shopping center at Jamboree Road and El Camino Real. Awards will be 
presented at 2 p.m. Sunday. The activities, including the awards ceremony, are 
open to public viewing. 
</P>
<P>
 "The competition represents one of many educational programs developed by the 
Home Builders Council in an effort to promote career awareness of the 
construction industry," Silverman said.BILL BILLITER 
</P>
