<TEXT>
<P>
 IBM Job Cuts Proceed Slowly: The computer giant said it has cut 20% to 23% of 
the 35,000 jobs it said it would eliminate by year's end.International Business 
Machines Corp. set that goal last July, saying it would reduce costs by $3 
billion this year. So far, between 7,000 and 8,000 jobs have been cut, an IBM 
spokesman said. That leaves 27,000 to 28,000 jobs to go over the next eight 
months. At IBM's annual meeting earlier this week, Chairman Louis V. Gerstner 
told shareholders the company will be profitable this year for the first time 
in four years. 
