<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Corporate Earnings 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA042994-0272 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 037111 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
April 29, 1994, Friday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Business; Part D; Page 2; Column 1; Financial Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
69 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fidelity National Financial Inc.: The Irvine title insurance underwriter 
posted a 58% gain in profit for the first quarter, to $6.8 million, or 43 cents 
a share, from $4.3 million, or 31 cents a share, for the 1993 quarter. Revenue 
increased 30% to $143.6 million from $110.4 million. The company attributed the 
results to the high level of home refinancing activity that continued into 
January and February. 
</P>
</TEXT>
