</P>
<P>
 junior, Irvine 
</P>
<P>
 "I believe that any conception or misconception of teens has to be based on 
the idea that teens are all similar -- which is to me a more ridiculous notion 
than all African-Americans are the same or all Mexican-Americans are the same. 
So I believe that the greatest misconception about teens is the belief that 
they can all be treated as equals." 
</P>
